{"at": "2026-05-31T19:00:33Z", "commit_ref": "a98d483", "decision": "include", "gate": "build", "rationale": "Spec 0022 A.1 adds the five new OpticalConstructor projects to Berreman.slnx; the existing build gate (dotnet build Berreman/Berreman.slnx -c Release, applies_to Berreman/**) already compiles all new code, so reuse it rather than add a constructor-specific build gate. filter:none, no select."}
{"at": "2026-05-31T19:00:33Z", "commit_ref": "a98d483", "decision": "include", "gate": "unit-tests", "rationale": "Spec A.2-A.3 reuse the Berreman engine (solver/field/material types) unchanged; the existing BerremanTests unit-tests gate guards against regressions in the reused engine the new projects consume. filter:none, no select."}
{"at": "2026-05-31T19:00:33Z", "commit_ref": "a98d483", "decision": "propose-new", "gate": "constructor-unit-tests", "rationale": "Operator requires the new code be testable via a UI-less surface first; spec A.6/P3 keeps model/update free of Avalonia types so the OpticalConstructor Domain/Storage/Optimization logic (beam-tree orchestration A.4/B, units spine A.10, JSON round-trip + schema validation A.7, optimization interface A.8, gradient discretize B.11) is UI-less testable. No existing gate runs tests over Berreman/OpticalConstructor/**; the unit-tests gate only targets BerremanTests. Filed in a NET-NEW OpticalConstructor group because the Berreman group is scoped to the pure solver, not the app/orchestration layer. TODO on: command (test project name/path is not named in the spec; inferred from the BerremanTests convention). draft authored at .proposed-gates/OpticalConstructor/constructor-unit-tests.gates with new-group .gates-md. filter:none, no select.", "draft_path": ".proposed-gates/OpticalConstructor/constructor-unit-tests.gates"}
